Review: Overall, very good service. On a busy night in Hayes, this is often the only Italian spot without a wait. The food isn’t extraordinary, but it’s reliable and the service is fast.
Excellent! Strongly recommend getting Chaat here — Pav bhajji, papdi chaat, samosa chaat, sev puri etc. The Kathi rolls and plates are okay, but the Chaat is where this place really shines.
Really amazing burger! Also great vibes/ambiance
Got some pizzas and apps, they were good. The pizza bread/crust was super fresh and perfect
Yum yum yum. Filling, reasonably priced, healthy

Awesome Peruvian restaurant in the Marina. Went for brunch, their empanadas were great. My friend got Pulpa (octopus) and said it was phenomenal. My only small complaint was that there weren’t many veggie options

PSA the back patio has really nice vibes, looks way nicer than their indoor seating or their frontside outdoor seating.
Ambiance is nice, and food was also good overall. I will say, you can definitely tell it’s vegan. Still giving it 4 stars because for an all-vegan restaurant, it’s pretty good
Good!
I found the food kind of bland and overpriced  - very possible we didn’t order the right things. Will go again since folks say it’s good!
One of the better places for Momos in the city

The Berkeley special sandwich is soooooooo good. Their homemade hummus is  incredible, I think this might be my favorite veggie sandwich of all time. Also great sit down vibes especially during the day - the back patio is elite! You could also grab a beer at Raleigh’s right next door

Great hole-in-the-wall spot in Chinatown. No reservation etc needed. Loved their deep fried veggie and meat dumplings (I know, deep frying dumplings sounds like a bit much but gosh it was so good). Also loved the general tso’s chicken and the chow mein!

5/5 for cheesecakes. My favorites - classic strawberry cheesecake, Godiva cheesecake, Dulce de leche & Salted caramel cheesecakes 

4/5 for rest of the food. The brown bread they give at the table is shockingly good but rest of the food wasn’t that great. Maybe I ordered the wrong things, I hear the Chipotle pasta is good?
Got takeout; did not disappoint!
One of the best places for upscale Chinese food in the city. They have veggie options too: Definitely a bit expensive, but worth!
It’s a wine bar in Hayes. It’s fine. Good selection of wines but kind of overpriced. Expected a bit more
One of the only spots for South Indian food in SF

This place is soooo good, is esp known for meat dishes. Yes it’s in the TL, but I can’t recommend it  enough. I got chicken 65 and lamb biryani - both incredible. On the veggie side, got pani puri, which slapped. i will regularly be craving this place!!!
Very cute spot adorned with old paintings, photographs and instruments. I’ve been here a couple times - the patatas bravas here are incredible, rest of the food is alright.
Solid ramen. Note - It’s located within Japan center mall and ambiance is okay. It can be pretty crowded too, so just keep wait times in mind
Food was a bit bland. You can tell that this place is catered to a non Indian audience
I like this place overall ! It’s cute and the food is decent.
Food was honestly meh but the view was spectacular. Suggest going here just for views + snacks/drinks
I was slightly disappointed by the food, especially given it’s such a pricey spot.
Little overpriced but yum yum
Amazing dim sum spot
1 word - delicious!!! This place changed my life
Go to spot in SF for food trucks with variety, drinks and chill vibes. Across the street is Stagecoach greens, with even more trucks and also a minigolf course.
Filling, tasty, fast. Love this place!
definitely on the pricier end of dim sum spots but food is really really yum 🤤🤤 the inside vibe is nice too.
Soooooo good.

I started questioning my own judgment about this place so I brought 3 vegetarians here and they LOVED IT. I mentioned in my last review, but at this place it just depends on what you order. For vegetarians, the saag paneer is fantastic, I also really liked the Bhindi. Pro tip - this place definitely caters to a large non-Indian/non-Nepali audience
Yum! Ariscault and Tartine are a tad better but La Boulangerie is also yum.
Been here a few times, have always really liked the  dishes - Potstickers, green beans, fried rice, firecracker wings, and spicy garlic noodles all really good.
Good happy hour! Nothing extraordinary but good food and vibes overall
On the pricier side but good food and views
It was good!!
It was good, liked the food - but didn’t find it exceptional per se. Still, one of the better Indian restaurants in SF (though I suppose that’s not saying much).

I found the food average. Kitchen story’s sister restaurants in SF like Surisan, Blackwood and Maple leaf are much better imo. Also the inside of Kitchen story is super stuffy/crowded, so much so that I couldn’t even hear my friend over the noise and over the adjacent table which was 1 foot away from me
Re reviewing as I just tried a new dish which changed my life - chicken keema biryani. best biryani in SF. Way better when the regular chicken biryani!
Never disappoints, even for vegetarians! The hand made pita, and the hummus / baba ganoush / labneh are my favorites

I can’t believe I’ve lived in SF for 4 years and never tried this spot. Their everything-crossaint is incredible; it has cream cheese stuffed inside and literally tastes like heaven. If I could eat this every day for breakfast I would. Their pistachio crossaint is also the best I’ve ever had. Great coffee too. Thanks for the rec @Ani!
Fantastic!!! The food and drinks were amazing. The ambiance is great and vibe is super lively too. 10/10 recommend!
Yummy brunch. Beware long lines, suggest coming on a weekday if possible
Been a couple times, the pizzas are pretty good and reliable. Not extraordinary, but still good.

The ambiance/vibe inside is so so nice. The drinks and desserts were also amazing. Food itself was mediocre though. Also very limited veggie options. Still giving it 4 stars for amazing ambiance, drinks and desserts.

Cute vibes (very instagrammable haha) and really great food. We went for brunch twice, and got their Cherry blossom tea set once (you have to specially request this 48 hours in advance via email, AFTER securing a reservation first - so it needs a bit of planning). The Tea set totally blew me away, it’s English style tea but with Japanese treats (e.g. mochi). Vegetarian friendly too! Definitely on the pricier side but well worth it for a special occasion!
So so good. The bread pudding and tres leches cakes are to die for. Careful though, they run out fast - suggest going as early as possible!
Liked my burrito, but salsas and sauces were kind of watery/runny

Fable is the most gorgeous restaurant in SF. This is my favorite date spot, favorite place to take my parents when they visit, and more. I would give the food 4 stars, but for the ambiance my overall rating is 5 stars here. The Grape Tartine is a must try, really yum dish.

Absolute favorite brunch spot in SF. Really nice vibes/ambiance, and top notch food. I found their meat stuff >>>> veggie stuff. I dream about the Chicken cup bap and Pimped Up Ramyun on a regular basis 😍
Great food and ambiance
As a North Indian who’s tried almost every spot in SF, this place wins hands down. Their food is flavorful, spicy and authentic. Highly recommend the biryani and curries (PTM, CTM).
This place is good, but a bit overpriced. They also discontinued the Tea leaf salad sadly.
Incredible Italian food in WeHo. good for large groups, good service, amazing ambiance (the inside is so pretty)

Amazing vibes, went on a Saturday afternoon and they had live music. It looks like you’re sitting inside a greenhouse. The food was great too. Def recommend as a lunch spot during Sonoma wine tastings!
I get takeout from here regularly, really good. Great veggie options too
good Italian food and good vibes!
Incredible pasta, the snail shell lumache is especially yum. Also had the house wine, which was very cheap (so really wasn’t expecting much) — but surprisingly good.
Great happy hour / drinks / dinner spot overlooking the bay bridge
The fried chicken, pad kee mau and roti dip all excellent. Thai ice tea also on point
I usually don’t get Avo toast anywhere but had heard especially good things about it here — and it was super super good. Also got French toast, which was alright, nothing that special.
10/10 food, drinks and vibes
Got takeout, found it very average
The restaurant itself is dimly late, so I tend to just get takeout. But the food is solid! Highly recommend the Bombay sandwiches here
The green sauce is basically crack 🤤 Most of the daily pizza flavors are great, but I do recommend checking the flavor of the day (and ensuring the ingredients sound good to you) before going
Love the Pad Thai and Tom yum here 🤤🤤 nice sit down spot, though it can get quite little loud/noisy inside
The best hot n honey pizza in the city. I’ve tried their pesto pizza and a few others; they’re all good but nothing comes close to their hot n honey! I usually remove the Copa and get it veggie:)

Sue me, I still really like this place for chaat 😭😭 big fan of their papdi chaat, chhole bhature and aloo tikki. Maybe it’s college nostalgia or maybe there’s just not many chaat places in SF. Will go back soon and re review!

Food: 4/5
Vibe & Ambiance: 4/5
Music: 3/5 (to be honest if you actually like jazz, this place sucks lol. I’ve been several times and found the music mediocre. Sorry!!)
Pretty average. I think people end up going here after drinking (at which point everything tastes good haha). IMO there’s at least 10 better ice cream spots in SF
This place is average at best.
Fried chicken sandwich and fries were 🔥
Food was very pricey but well worth. Incredible views and location!
I love this place! The paella and churros were especially good
This place sucks for vegetarians. If you eat meat, I do STRONGLY recommend this spot. Some of the best meat curries I’ve had in SF.
